notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Start Backup Process
components.description: Initializes the backup workflow and triggers the date check task.

components.name: Determine Backup Strategy
components.description: Checks the day of week and routes execution to the full or incremental backup task.

components.name: Perform Full Backup
components.description: Executes a simulated full database backup on Saturdays.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when date_check_task routes to full_backup_task (Saturday)

components.name: Perform Incremental Backup
components.description: Executes a simulated incremental backup of changed data on weekdays.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when date_check_task routes to incremental_backup_task (weekday)

components.name: Verify Backup Integrity
components.description: Validates backup integrity after either full or incremental backup completes.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after at least one backup task succeeds (trigger_rule none_failed_min_one_success)

components.name: Backup Workflow Completion
components.description: Marks the backup workflow as completed after verification.

description.description: Comprehensive pipeline that selects a backup strategy (full on Saturday, incremental on weekdays) and verifies the backup.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

provide_context.description: Provide execution context to the Python callable

sleep_seconds.description: Simulated execution duration for full backup
Simulated execution duration for incremental backup

trigger_rule.description: Trigger rule for merge point ensuring execution after at least one branch succeeds

sources: DAG trigger (execution date context) that initiates the backup workflow
sinks: Backup workflow completion marker (final EmptyOperator task)
intermediate_datasets: Simulated full backup dataset (produced by full_backup_task)
Simulated incremental backup dataset (produced by incremental_backup_task)
